# Lookup Entities & Hibernate L2 Cache

## Lookup Entity â€” Standard Lombok Stack

```java
@Entity
@Immutable
@Cacheable
@Cache(usage = CacheConcurrencyStrategy.READ_ONLY)
@Getter
@NoArgsConstructor
@EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true)
@Table(name = "pp_pre_check_statuses")
public class PreCheckStatusEntity {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    @Column(name = "pk_pre_check_status")
    @EqualsAndHashCode.Include
    private Long id;

    @Column(name = "name", nullable = false)
    private String name;

    @Column(name = "description", columnDefinition = "TEXT")
    private String description;
}
```

**Required annotations:**
| Annotation | Why |
|---|---|
| `@Immutable` | Hibernate skips dirty checks, never generates UPDATE/DELETE |
| `@Cacheable` | Marks entity as eligible for L2 caching |
| `@Cache(usage = CacheConcurrencyStrategy.READ_ONLY)` | Most efficient strategy for immutable data |
| `@Getter` | Read access only |
| `@NoArgsConstructor` | Required by JPA |
| `@EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true)` | Identity-based equality |

**Forbidden:** `@Setter`, `@Data`, `@AllArgsConstructor`, `@Builder`

**Do NOT** extend `BaseEntity` â€” lookup entities are static reference data, no audit timestamps.

## Hibernate L2 Cache

Only **lookup entities** are cached. Domain entities are NOT cached.

### Required Cache Annotations
Both `@Cacheable` (JPA) + `@Cache` (Hibernate) must be present:
- `@Cacheable` tells the persistence provider the entity is cacheable
- `@Cache(usage = READ_ONLY)` configures the strategy â€” matches `@Immutable`

### Configuration (`application.properties`)
```properties
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.cache.use_second_level_cache=true
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.cache.region.factory_class=jcache
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.javax.cache.uri=classpath:ehcache.xml
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.javax.cache.missing_cache_strategy=fail
```

`missing_cache_strategy=fail` â€” app refuses to start if a `@Cacheable` entity has no region in `ehcache.xml`. Prevents silently unbounded caches.

### Ehcache Regions (`ehcache.xml`)
Every `@Cacheable` lookup entity **must** have a `<cache>` region (alias = entity's FQCN).

```xml
<cache-template name="lookup-cache">
    <heap unit="entries">500</heap>
    <expiry><ttl unit="hours">1</ttl></expiry>
</cache-template>

<cache alias="com.arrise.daily_roster.entities.lookups.PreCheckStatusEntity"
       uses-template="lookup-cache"/>
```

When adding a new lookup entity, **always add a corresponding `<cache>` region** â€” otherwise the app fails to start.
